over their current allocations.) We show that the region allocated
to each center $\xi$ is a union of finitely many bounded connected
sets. However, in the case of a Poisson process, an infinite volume
of sites are allocated to centers further away than $\xi$. We prove
power law lower bounds on the allocation distance of a typical site.
It is an open problem to prove any upper bound in d{\textgreater}1.},
